An inquest in January 2012 heard Daniel complained of feeling unwell after taking part in a drinking game and was ‘completely out of it’.

Party hostess Danielle Baker, 24, told the hearing: ‘The paramedics told him he needed to sleep.

‘After they left, he was sick and his lips turned blue. We called a second ambulance which arrived nearly half an hour after the first one left.’

Mr Powell told the hearing: ‘In the back of my mind was the thought to take him to hospital. But we left him. His friends were saying to let him sleep it off and we were swayed by the environment. 

