'He was in a quiet place with people he knew. If it was a pub, club or raucous party I might have taken a different decision.’

Gwent coroner David Bowen had recorded a narrative verdict on the death of Mr Cripps, of Maesglas, Newport, adding: ‘With hindsight he should have been taken to hospital.’

Mr Cripps’s family are taking legal action against the ambulance service.

